"&#xa0;\nUK Environmental Law Association – Supplementary written evidenceSupplementary written evidence for the Joint Committee on the draft Deregulation Bill: clause 47(3)\n&#xa0;\nIntroductory comments&#xa0;\nComments on Compatibility of Clause 47(3) with the Aarhus Convention&#xa0;\nPUBLIC PARTICIPATION DURING THE PREPARATION OF EXECUTIVE REGULATIONS AND/OR GENERALLY APPLICABLE LEGALLY BINDING NORMATIVE INSTRUMENTS\n&#xa0;\nthat\n&#xa0;\nEach Party shall strive to promote effective public participation at an appropriate stage, and while options are still open, during the \npreparation by public authorities of executive regulations and other generally applicable legally binding rules that may have a significant effect on the environment.  …\n&#xa0;\nthe repeal of this provision\n would seem to represent a threat to compliance with the UK’s obligations under Aarhus.  \n&#xa0;\n29\nth\n October 2013\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"